    From the manufacturer

    Introducing: The Portofino Collection

    Read more

    Brilliant Blues

    Distinct dishes and eye-catching design come together in this new, versatile series from Corelle.

    Whether it’s a casual gathering or a romantic dinner, Corelle Style is made for modern dining and entertaining. With a range of shapes, styles and trends, you’ll find the perfect dinnerware for any occasion.

    Read more

    Dinner Plate

    An intricate pattern brings the rustic charm of the Italian coast to these dinner plates.

    Lunch Plate

    Add the rustic charm of coastal Italy to any meal with these salad plates.

    Appetizer Plate

    These snack plates bring the essence of coastal Italy to your table.

    Bowl

    Serve up a taste of coastal Italian charm with these medium bowls.

    Read more

    Read more

    Product description

    Seaside towns on the Italian coast inspired this intricate pattern in classic shades of blue with the casual beauty of hand-painted tiles you’ll set a perfectly charming table indoors or out.

    Care Instructions: (1) DO NOT use to microwave popcorn or to hold or support popcorn bags, microwave convenience foods with special browning wrappers, etc. Some convenience food packaging is designed to heat rapidly in a microwave oven and may cause breakage (2) DO NOT heat an empty vessel in a microwave oven. It may become too hot to handle, crack or break (3) DO NOT heat a small amount of food in larger dish in a microwave oven. It may become too hot to handle, crack or break (4) DO NOT overheat oil or butter in microwave. Use minimum amount of cooking time (5) DO NOT use or repair any item that is chipped, cracked, or severely scratched. Damaged items may break or shatter without warning (6) DO NOT abuse by dropping or hitting against a hard object (7) DO NOT use abrasive cleanser, scouring pads, or any object that will scratch items.

        How are ratings calculated?
        To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we don’t use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzes reviews to verify trustworthiness.

        4.0 out of 5 stars Beautiful but not perfect
        Reviewed in the United States on November 23, 2019
        Verified Purchase
        Correlle dishes are excellent and the Portofino design is beautiful, light weight, and I love them.

        Note that the color is not consistent on all the plates.
        See the picture I attached, 3 plates, 3 shades
        Some would be annoyed by it. I think it makes it look hand-made.

        Also, the soup bowl shape is different than the other Corelle set I have, and Portofino bowls do not stuck well.
        6 of them takes more than double the space of 6 regular Corelle bowls.

        Last comment, this set is missing the 8-1/2-inch salad/lunch plates. Instead, there are the smaller 6-3/4 inch appetizer/snack plates.
        Given a choice, I would skip the not so great soup bowls, and get just plates in 3 sizes

        5.0 out of 5 stars L♥VE This Pattern ♥♥♥
        Reviewed in the United States on October 12, 2019
        Verified Purchase
        This is my all-time favorite pattern from Corelle. I first purchased the set of 6 luncheon plates as that's the size we eat our meals on. I fell in love with the pattern, the colors of blues, the rustic, old-world look and feel. These are perfect in my blue Italian kitchen. We come from the coast of Tuscany so these were made for my family.
        I then bought the dinner set -- 2 of them and also 2 more sets of 6 luncheon plates. The luncheon plates arrived in about 1.5 months. The complete set arrived in about 2 months, after the last 2 orders of luncheon plates arrived and I'm still waiting on the 2nd complete set to arrive in a few more weeks.
        This is the last set of dishes I will ever want to buy. I love everything about Corelle and especially mixed with this design.
        I paid full price for my dishes. Let me know if you have any questions.

        * Oh no - my last complete dinnerware set arrived and one small plate is broken in half with a few shards off of it.
        * Returned the broken set; received the new set and only 5 bowls. Sent back and waiting to see if they will send out a new set or not.
        *Reached out to Corning at the link posted to other questioners and haven't heard anything back about the broken plate, it's been weeks. I'll just keep returning the whole dinner set until one arrives not broken and with all pieces included. Seems it would have been easier to just send out a replacement broken dish.

        KarenH
        5.0 out of 5 stars These are so light you'll fall in love
        Reviewed in the United States on October 23, 2019
        Verified Purchase
        I am recovering from a partially torn rotator cuff, and let me tell you that among the minor impositions it poses is lifting dishes: to set the table, to load and unload the dishwasher. You wouldn't think that the weight of plates would be a big deal, but if you've ever had a sore shoulder you can understand IT'S A BIG DEAL. Well, no longer. These dishes are so light that I'm back in business. Game changer! Now are the they the most beautiful dishes I own? Nah. But they are...attractive. And while I gave them five stars on durability and sturdiness, that is based on the fact that they shipped with barely any packaging (!) and arrived completely intact, without a chip or a scratch in the bunch. If I drop one on the tile floor I doubt it will hold up, but then nothing does. Five stars from me, all around.
